## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
1. **Compilation check**: `cargo check --workspace` — all types, traits, and modules must resolve
2. **Unit tests** for `SparseCode` Pod/Zeroable guarantees: `cargo test -p nexus-core`
3. **Metal shader compilation**: `build.rs` must successfully produce `weaver.metallib` (requires Xcode + Metal SDK)

### Manual Verification
1. Verify `SparseCode` is exactly 16 bytes via `std::mem::size_of::<SparseCode>()` assert in tests
2. Verify `Fabric` alignment is 16384 via `std::mem::align_of::<Fabric<Llama8B>>()` assert in tests
3. Run `cargo doc --workspace --no-deps` and verify documentation renders correctly

> [!NOTE]
> The Metal kernel and full mlx-rs integration will require an M1+ Mac with Xcode 16.2+. The Rust type system and module structure can be verified on any platform.
